stream
BT
/F1 11 Tf
72 740 Td
14 TL
(- zod: request validation) Tj
T*
(- bcrypt: password hashing) Tj
T*
(- jsonwebtoken: token generation and verification) Tj
T*
(- helmet, cors, cookie-parser: API security and cookie parsing) Tj
T*
(- morgan + winston: request and structured logging) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6\) Typical Execution Flow \(Signup\)) Tj
T*
(User sends POST /api/auth/sign-up with name/email/password.) Tj
T*
(-> signup schema validates the body.) Tj
T*
(-> createUser checks for existing email.) Tj
T*
(-> password is hashed with bcrypt.) Tj
T*
(-> user row is inserted into users table.) Tj
T*
(-> JWT token is generated.) Tj
T*
(-> token is set in an HTTP-only cookie.) Tj
T*
(-> API responds with 201 and user payload.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(7\) Strengths and Tradeoffs) Tj
T*
(Strengths:) Tj
T*
(- Clear layered boundaries \(route/controller/service/model/validation\).) Tj
T*
(- Security baseline present \(hashing, JWT, HTTP-only cookies, helmet\).) Tj
T*
(- Migration-backed relational schema with structured logging.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Tradeoffs / watchouts:) Tj
T*
(- sign-in and sign-out are still placeholders.) Tj
T*
(- Error handling is not centralized via a global error middleware.) Tj
T*
(- A few naming and consistency issues can cause runtime bugs.) Tj
T*
(- Email uniqueness is enforced in code but not yet at DB constraint level.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(8\) Final Summary) Tj
T*
(This is a layered Express monolith that implements the foundation of an auth API.) Tj
T*
(Requests flow from routes to controllers to services to Drizzle/Postgres, with Zod) Tj
T*
(validation,) Tj
T*
(JWT cookies, and Winston logging across the stack. It is a solid starter architecture with) Tj
T*
(clear) Tj
T*
(separation of concerns, but auth completeness and production hardening still need follow-up) Tj
T*
(work.) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
